{
  "stem": "2435.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she packed all the things for us that we were able to take along-- were not too many things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, my father-- we lived from the pension that my dad had received, because he worked for quite a few years in Breslau.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had also worked in Berlin before we had moved to Breslau.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we-- he got a pension.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Actually, that was all we lived on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We moved to a different place in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was a place where we also immigrated from, Heilbronner Strasse, which was near-- by [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there my grandmother, the mother of my mother, lived with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Charlotte Ochs.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was-- I remember I was very attached to my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather, her husband, died already in 1927.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was a conductor of the Philharmonic Core in Berlin, quite a famous man.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were glad that he didn't live through all that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the mother of my mother-- of my father, died already in 19-- I think-- '27 too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the father of my father died 1918.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they did not live at that time anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Paternal grand--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's mother, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was a writer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She wrote books.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were published.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was quite an intelligent and-- person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But strangely enough, I was more attached to my other grandmother, the mother of my mother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Somehow, I felt more at ease with her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And actually, even though later on we were not able to get a visa for her, she was a one to whom I turned at times of misery, where I was so unhappy.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, in Berlin, I was able to attend a kindergarten school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was always glad to work with children.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
